howPublicProfile?language=EN>Drab Counterpoint</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.csh.rit.edu/~marius/eq/bored/brane.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/24/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>7:50:40 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: your equip doesn't suck</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hah no way. There isnt a single player good enough to dodge a mobs attack. AC/HP helps there, go wear some crap armor and try to take hits. Or you could be the best at timing that charm so that it would recharm with no time or mana lost, or maybe able to keep the rhythym to lock down 4 mobs with a mez, but what good is it when they resist too much because of low CHA? Want your melee attack to be worth more than an OOM wizard, then get good weapons since a bard's melee is on the weaker side anyway. I could be the greatest player in the world but auto-attack is just that.. auto. Unless you're trying to raise wisdom or something, yeah equipment matters.. a lot.<br>
<br>
You can't avoid the fact that equipment plays a large role. Skill is a factor up to a certain point. Most of the work is done by random numbers generated and checked against certain bounds. Good equipment and level will change those bounds in your favor. A good player can only generate those random numbers at the right time.</font><P><hr><br>
Drab<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulaian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulaian</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>I live here.... get out.</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/25/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>7:28:46 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: your equip doesn't suck</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Actually, AC from armor has zero effect on your ability to avoid getting hit, what it affects is the amount of damage you take when you do get hit. Avoiding hits is based on defense, dodge, parry, riposte and block.Yes, equipment is important, but it is not indispensable. Skill is indispensable. In -most- groups, one can get around the need of getting hit at all with some adaption. For instance, if you have a high enough person pulling, who is sufficiently skilled, you will rarely have to mez/charm a mob at all as you can be spoon fed single pulls. With a good taunting tank, there should be little risk of a bard getting agroed by the mob currently in melee either. And if you do take a few hits, that ain't gonna kill you either.<br>
<br>
For bards, I know that such things as instruments do have a large impact on the performance of your various songs, but as this topic was about armor/weapons then, unless you are primary tank in a group (granted, it happens sometimes, bards are pretty good at absorbing damage now) there is really no need to get hit under normal circumstances, and thus no serious need for the best armor. As for weapons, well, they're nice, but bards lack double attack to make them really useful. Basically, playing with less than perfect equipment is a challenge that good players can adapt to, but bad ones will get killed by. Its all about adaption, say, if you're not confident you can mez a mob, have someone else park it instead. Just because you are a bard does not mean you -have- to fall into the stereotype of mez/charm/haste/regen/mana all the time. As I see it, the single greatest strength of bards is versatility, but you just told me it is gear... well, I disagree<br>
<br>
So, to sum up, I would rather be grouped with a naked bard who knows his/her class well, than a bard twink in full singing steel who thinks playing Jonathan's Whistling Warsong all the time is super l33t because it makes himself (and only himself) attack faster. So, if your armor is not good, don't get hit. If your weapons are not good, concentrate on songs instead to maximize the efficiency of other melees. And if your instruments suck... well... go get better ones hehe. And while stats do have an effect on your success with mez, charm etc, that effect is quite small except when dealing with mobs near your own level. As for trying to wear crap armor and taking hits... well... I am a ranger <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   My AC at lvl 55 is only just past 800 unbuffed, yet I do fine. Why? Because I know how not to get agroed. Instead I concentrate on dealing as much damage as I can, while letting the main tank keep agro. Again, adaption. You're an extremely versatile class, don't tell me that without your high end armor you're useless, because you are not. And despite you saying that, I doubt you really think so either. Or you wouldn't be a bard still <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Btw, when I said moderate armor, keep in mind that moderate does not have to be leather or something similar. At 60, moderate could well be top of the line armor to a lvl 50.<br>
<br>
[Edit] Spelling. Btw, I like this discussion about skill vs gear, keep it going.</font><P>Ulaian Moonleaf <BR>
